<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,637,950]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Geiger" box="[274,537,637,662]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Geiger, D. L. &amp; Owen, B. (2012) Abalone: World-wide Haliotidae. ConchBooks, Hackenheim, viii + 361 pp." type="book" year="2012">
Geiger &amp; Owen (
<number box="[470,529,638,662]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
I have not assigned the South African 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1069,637,662]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Haliotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1069,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Haliotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species to subgenera, due to the lack of a robust phylogenetic framework upon which to base subdivision of the genus. Surprisingly, given the morphological diversity evident, the five species comprising the largely endemic South African radiation cluster as a monophyletic lineage in molecular analyses (Bester-van der 
<bibRefCitation author="Merwe" box="[889,1114,745,770]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Bester-van der Merwe, A. E., D'Amato, M. E., Swart, B. L. &amp; Roodt-Wilding, R. (2012) Molecular phylogeny of South African abalone, its origin and evolution as revealed by two genes. Marine Biology Research, 8, 727 - 736. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000.2012.678856" type="journal article" year="2012">
Merwe 
<emphasis box="[980,1033,745,770]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1053,1114,746,770]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). If further research with a broader sampling of taxa confirms this, then two names are available for this group, 
<taxonomicName authority="Montfort, 1910" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1910" box="[1094,1372,781,806]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Padollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1094,1194,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Padollus</emphasis>
Montfort, 
<number box="[1316,1372,782,806]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</taxonomicName>
[
<typeStatus box="[1385,1436,782,806]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species (o.d.): 
<taxonomicName authority="Montfort, 1810" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[321,741,817,842]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Padollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rubicundus">
<emphasis box="[321,556,817,842]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Padollus rubicundus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort" box="[567,741,817,842]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Montfort, P. D. de (1810) Conchyliologie systematique, et classification methodique des coquilles, offrant leurs figures, leur arrangement generique, leurs descriptions caracteristiques, leurs noms: ainsi que leur synonymie en plusiers langues. Coquilles univalves, non cloisonnees. Vol. 2. Schoell, Paris, 676 pp." type="book" year="1810">
Montfort, 
<number box="[685,741,818,842]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1810.0">1810</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[761,803,818,841]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">non</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roding" box="[813,970,817,842]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Roding, P. F. (1798) Museum Boltenianum sive catalogus cimeliorum e tribus regnis naturae quae olim collegerat Joa. Fried. Bolten, M. D. p. d. Pars secunda continens Conchylia sive Testacea univalvia, bivalvia et multivalvia. J. C. Trappii, Hamburg, viii + 199 pp." type="book" year="1798">
RÃ¶ding, 
<number box="[913,970,818,842]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1798.0">1798</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) = 
<taxonomicName box="[1004,1170,817,842]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Haliotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis box="[1004,1170,817,842]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Haliotis parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wenz, 1938" authorityName="Wenz" authorityYear="1938" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotididae" genus="Euhaliotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1240,1356,817,842]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Euhaliotis</emphasis>
Wenz, 
<number box="[151,207,854,878]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1938.0">1938</number>
</taxonomicName>
[
<typeStatus box="[223,274,854,878]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species (o.d.): 
<taxonomicName box="[454,623,853,878]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Haliotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="midae">
<emphasis box="[454,623,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Haliotis midae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Since 
<taxonomicName authority="Montfort, 1810" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" box="[721,820,853,878]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Padollus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,820,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Padollus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the older name, it has priority over 
<taxonomicName box="[1276,1391,853,878]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotididae" genus="Euhaliotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1391,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Euhaliotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Haliotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pustulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. pustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be referable to 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams, 1854" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1854" box="[500,956,889,914]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Sulculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,595,889,914]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Sulculus</emphasis>
H. Adams &amp; A. Adams, 
<number box="[897,956,889,914]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1854.0">1854</number>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the affinity of 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1407,889,914]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haliotidae" genus="Haliotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="unilateralis">
<emphasis box="[1241,1407,889,914]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. unilateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is uncertain.
</paragraph>
